  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a chat user, I want to see the real unread message count so that I can know how many unread messages there are.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nStatus currently shows unread message counts as `9+` when there are more than 9 unread messages. In common usage this means that chats always tend to show 9+ and offer no context or insight into how many messages are actually unread.  It could be 10 or 945.\r\n\r\nBy showing the true count we can better inform users to how active a chat is and help them understand how many unread without the need to go into each chat. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nChat badge count shows actual number if more than 9\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nShows 9+\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\nFor both mobile and desktop.\r\n\r\nDiscussion: We may want to show 999+ or 9999+ or some upper limit otherwise it could go a bit nuts?\r\n\r\ncc @errorists ",
