    "body": "Here are mobile badges for reference\r\n<img width=\"580\" alt=\"slice\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4932774/48609294-cdf25b00-e983-11e8-8021-22289163f826.png\">\r\n\r\ncc @EugeOrtiz for desktop\r\n\r\n@chadyj should this include the total unread badge next to the Home icon (space constrained but it's doable) and the badges next to the 'Back' arrow when inside a chat (space constrained and not doable, we can't add additional digits there)? Honestly, I always found the badge next to 'Back' arrow totally unnecessary but that's me :) after 1000 we can also do 1K+, 2K+, to cap it at a reasonable 3 character limit. Otherwise, 999+ sounds ok.\r\n\r\n",
